default&#xa0;defaultMr Hurd:default At one level, the thing we are most concerned about is getting the data out. That requires will more than anything else at the moment. What we are trying to construct is mechanisms whereby the Government has access to people with superb data skills and data knowledge. We have a group of very competent civil servants leading this at the Cabinet Office, but our main challenge is working with other Departments to get them over the line in terms of releasing data.
